1
00:01:34,560 --> 00:01:35,600
9.8 grams.

2
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:41,600
Master, please weigh it again.

3
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:43,080
Yes, one more time.

4
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:49,000
It's 9.8 grams.

5
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:49,840
Still 9.8.

6
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:51,520
We did it! We finally did it!

7
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:52,200
We did it!

8
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,000
We did it!

9
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,880
Old Xuan, Old Man.

10
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:59,280
You've all worked so hard.

11
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:01,840
Thank you, everyone.

12
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:05,920
Where's Zhang Du?

13
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:07,000
Zhang Du.

14
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:10,360
He's been asleep since he passed out.

15
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:11,520
He hasn't woken up yet.

16
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,840
Don't worry.

17
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,400
He collapsed,

18
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,920
but not for real.

19
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:17,240
He just fell asleep from exhaustion.

20
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:19,160
I just checked on him. Don't worry.

21
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:23,080
Alright, don't disturb him.

22
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:24,720
Let him sleep well.

23
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:25,800
Yeah.

24
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:50,080
Take a look. What do you think?

25
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:52,360
It's over-processed.

26
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:53,920
Is it serious?

27
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,200
Pretty bad, yeah.

28
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:58,640
Over-processed.

29
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:02,080
That means the paper won't absorb ink.

30
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:04,920
How did that happen?

31
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:07,360
We wanted the paper thin and smooth.

32
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:09,280
So we added too much kiwi vine sap.

33
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:11,080
And that causes this kind of problem.

34
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:15,160
Then we've got to fix it.

35
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,440
Old Xuan.

36
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:19,800
What Jingbo aims for this time

37
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:21,720
is restoring Republican-era documents.

38
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:26,080
They need thinness and toughness.

39
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,920
Writing on it isn't the main use.

40
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:29,800
Master Man.

41
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:31,720
I've done ancient book restoration before.

42
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:32,720
There are always missing pieces

43
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:34,520
that restorers need to write in.

44
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,400
That's right.

45
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:37,720
This time,

46
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:41,360
this came up because of your Jingbo order.

47
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:47,200
But we're making Chengxintang paper together.

48
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:48,800
Masters,

49
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,320
you're both right.

50
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:51,200
But the thing is,

51
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:54,320
I've already reported to my superiors and Jingbo.

52
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:56,960
And our chairman is busy preparing

53
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,640
a grand launch ceremony.

54
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:00,360
Are you kidding me?

55
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:03,520
Nothing's even close to being ready,

56
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:05,640
and you're holding a launch ceremony?

57
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:07,360
I compared it with the original paper,

58
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:08,400
and did physical and chemical tests.

59
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,920
The data all looked fine.

60
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,600
It's just that I was being a bit selfish.

61
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:15,120
I spoke too soon and reported it up.

62
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:16,959
It's my fault for being hasty.

63
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:17,800
Masters,

64
00:04:17,959 --> 00:04:18,800
please, take a look.

65
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:20,600
Is there any good way now

66
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,079
we can sort this out ourselves?

67
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:27,760
I'll give it a try.

68
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:28,400
Good.

69
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:31,360
There's one thing to handle first.

70
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,640
This over-processed paper issue,

71
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,600
we've run into it before.

72
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:40,880
But if it's severely over-processed,

73
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:43,600
then it's a paper defect.

74
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:46,080
Whether you can fix it is hard to say.

75
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:48,280
The point is, you've already reported it.

76
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:49,520
If you try to go back on it now,

77
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:52,200
that'll be tough.

78
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:56,240
So I suggest handling this carefully.

79
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:57,920
Tell your superiors

80
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,880
to prepare for the worst.

81
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:06,080
Master Xuan, how about this?

82
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,600
We take a two-pronged approach.

83
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,640
The Chengxintang launch goes ahead,

84
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:11,920
and we work on fixing the paper defect.

85
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,520
They don't interfere, and nothing gets delayed.

86
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:15,200
Isn't that just deception?

87
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:17,200
I, this, this...

88
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:19,400
How is that deception?

89
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:20,520
Let me tell you,

90
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:21,920
we absolutely can't do this.

91
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:24,800
If it works, it works. If not, it doesn't.

92
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,600
Passing off failure as success,

93
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,640
that's not what the Xuan family does.

94
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:32,680
Can't we be a bit flexible, though?

95
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,040
Yongnian.

96
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:39,600
The chairman's side is manageable.

97
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:41,920
It's mainly Jingbo pushing hard,

98
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:45,360
that's why the launch date was set.

99
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,200
Yeah, Master Xuan.

100
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,320
Personally, I don't mind.

101
00:05:48,320 --> 00:05:50,240
But we've already reported to Jingbo.

102
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:52,000
We said it's done, and now saying it isn't,

103
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,240
flip-flopping back and forth,

104
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:54,440
what we'll lose

105
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:56,800
is the Hongxing Factory's reputation.

106
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:11,000
When's your press conference scheduled?

107
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:12,080
This Saturday.

108
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:14,240
Today's already Wednesday.

109
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,800
That means we only have two and a half days.

110
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:17,320
Right.

111
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:21,680
Old Man, that method you mentioned...

112
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:24,640
Rewet the paper,

113
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:27,240
then dry it on wooden boards.

114
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,640
That's the only way left.

115
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,560
Then let's give it a try.

116
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:39,320
Re-drying it on wooden boards,

117
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:40,440
will that actually work?

118
00:06:41,320 --> 00:06:44,240
It loosens the paper's fiber structure.

119
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,920
In theory, it's feasible.

120
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:50,200
For over a century after the Southern Tang,

121
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:54,880
the Chengxintang paper technique was lost.

122
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:58,920
Until Song dynasty Xuan ancestors

123
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:01,520
recreated it using sandalwood bark.

124
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:03,000
So here's the question:

125
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,440
why was it lost?

126
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:07,320
Because it's hard.

127
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,360
That's why you all can't make it.

128
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,240
Nothing to be ashamed of.

129
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,880
That's not right, Director Liao.

130
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:15,120
Chengxintang paper was lost

131
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:17,200
because Li Yu issued a decree

132
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:19,200
banning its private production and trade.

133
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:20,880
Then Southern Tang fell,

134
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:23,240
and that's when the craft was lost.

135
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,240
That's one interpretation.

136
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:27,360
It was so scarce that

137
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:30,640
Su Shi described Chengxintang paper

138
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:33,440
like getting a celestial sphere or gongbi.

139
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:34,640
What does that mean?

140
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:37,200
Wasn't it Ouyang Xiu who said that?

141
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:39,000
Right, right, Ouyang Xiu.

142
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:42,440
Ouyang Xiu, yes. This "celestial sphere",

143
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:43,680
let me test you, what does it mean?

144
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:45,880
You're going off-topic, Director Liao.

145
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:46,880
This "celestial sphere"

146
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:48,880
was an ancient astronomical instrument.

147
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:52,680
And the gongbi was a precious ritual jade.

148
00:07:52,760 --> 00:07:53,640
Ouyang Xiu

149
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:58,680
called Chengxintang paper a treasure of heaven and earth.

150
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,440
Just get straight to the solution, please.

151
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:03,560
I've explained this much

152
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:04,880
and you still don't get it?

153
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:07,440
The solution

154
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:09,440
is that there is no solution.

155
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:12,440
Come on, everybody stop working.

156
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:13,640
Come over here.

157
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:20,680
Old Man, it's no use.

158
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:21,720
Yes.

159
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:23,160
Old Xuan.

160
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,560
I'll call the chairman

161
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:27,520
and have him postpone the press conference.

162
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:28,320
Master Man,

163
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:30,240
how do we explain this to Jingbo?

164
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:32,559
The chairman must explain it himself.

165
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:33,640
That won't work.

166
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:35,679
Media and officials have been notified.

167
00:08:35,679 --> 00:08:37,000
If we postpone now,

168
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,760
we'd be ruining everything.

169
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,360
When I was little,

170
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:43,440
my grandpa told me a method.

171
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,440
He said you take two wooden boards

172
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:47,760
and clamp the paper between them,

173
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:50,000
then hammer it,

174
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:53,000
which loosens the paper's fibers.

175
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:55,280
Master.

176
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,920
That method sounds promising.

177
00:08:58,920 --> 00:08:59,720
Master Xuan,

178
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:02,120
what you just said reminded me.

179
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:06,000
Ancient books have similar records.

180
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:10,120
Director Liao, quick, which book?

181
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:12,560
Don't rush me, let me think.

182
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:17,800
Siku...

183
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,320
In the "Siku Quanshu",

184
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:23,760
there's Cao Zhao's "Gegu Yaolun".

185
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:26,360
"Gegu Yaolun" records a similar method.

186
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:28,880
Daya Studio has the "Siku Quanshu".

187
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:30,880
I'll call Boss Xin right away.

188
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,560
Good, make the call.

189
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:33,320
I'll head over now.

190
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:33,880
Hurry, go.

191
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:34,640
I'll go too.

192
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:35,320
Let's go.

193
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:40,000
Let me ask, Director Liao,

194
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,760
did you actually see it in that ancient book,

195
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:46,120
and did it actually solve the problem?

196
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:10,880
"Siku Quanshu," "Gegu Yaolun"...

197
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:12,520
It's divided into three volumes, thirteen essays.

198
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:14,400
Covering ancient bronzes, paintings, and rubbings.

199
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:15,520
Quite a lot of content.

200
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:17,360
It's fine. Let me look for it.

201
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:29,720
Be careful.

202
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:30,240
Okay.

203
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,360
Careful not to mess things up.

204
00:10:31,760 --> 00:10:32,520
Got it.

205
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:44,400
Careful.

206
00:10:58,640 --> 00:10:59,640
Is this the one?

207
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:04,120
"Gegu Yaolun."

208
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:08,360
Yes.

209
00:11:13,160 --> 00:11:14,640
Hey, where are you going?

210
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:16,760
Zhang Du!

211
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:20,280
I'm taking it home to read it properly.

212
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:25,120
Taozi.

213
00:11:25,280 --> 00:11:27,640
These books have never left the archive.

214
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:29,520
Sister Xin, I'll go tell him right now.

215
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:30,520
I'm going right now.

216
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:32,120
Zhang Du! Zhang Du!

217
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:49,600
The ancestors' first bit of wisdom

218
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:52,040
was to take these layers of paper

219
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:53,440
and stack them like this

220
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,680
When pounded down, they create

221
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:57,920
a collective resonance

222
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:02,680
This vibration opens up the gaps

223
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,480
between the fibers of each sheet

224
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:06,240
fixing the flaw where its extreme thinness

225
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:08,360
causes poor ink conductivity.

226
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,720
is thereby resolved.

227
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:12,720
And what's the ancestors' second wisdom?

228
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:15,480
Each divider holds only ten sheets

229
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:19,240
Only with ten sheets can this pounding

230
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:22,360
distribute the force evenly on each sheet

231
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:25,760
bonding the fibers more tightly together

232
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:27,320
enhancing the toughness

233
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:29,920
This is Chengxintang paper's

234
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:32,760
unique manufacturing process

235
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:37,160
It differs from our regular Xuan paper

236
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:49,200
We are witnessing at this moment

237
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:51,680
a historic breakthrough in the Xuan paper industry.

238
00:12:51,760 --> 00:12:54,040
Hongxing Factory, representing national Xuan paper enterprises,

239
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:54,920
has joined forces with the Xuan Family paper mill,

240
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:57,720
an honored national intangible cultural heritage inheritor.

241
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:59,480
Over three years of joint research

242
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:01,800
they have successfully revived Chengxintang paper.

243
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:04,040
This paper, once praised by ancient literary masters as

244
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:07,040
an imperial paper with "skin like eggshell, pure as jade,"

245
00:13:07,040 --> 00:13:07,600
Today

246
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,920
before the Beijing Museum expert panel

247
00:13:09,920 --> 00:13:11,120
its brilliance shines once again

248
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:13,800
Just now, Beijing Museum expert Prof. Wang Yanxi

249
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:16,320
used an electron microscope to check the fibers

250
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:17,120
He concluded that

251
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:20,040
pounding qingtan bark for 1,000 days,

252
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:22,480
mixed with modern nano-filtration tech,

253
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:24,360
fully matches the museum collection's

254
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:27,040
Song dynasty Chengxintang paper specs.

255
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:28,560
How can this host exaggerate so much?

256
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:30,000
"Over three years," seriously?

257
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,160
Now we're famous.

258
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:32,800
Making the Chengxintang paper

259
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:35,280
took under half a month, start to finish.

260
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:39,000
What's nano-filtration technology?

261
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:40,640
Who knows?

262
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:42,520
I think either Hongxing factory

263
00:13:42,520 --> 00:13:44,040
or the TV station just made it up

264
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:45,600
What are you talking about?

265
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:47,200
I've lived my whole life

266
00:13:47,640 --> 00:13:49,240
and still don't know what "nano" is

267
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:50,160
Or how you eat it

268
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:53,720
You only know how to eat.

269
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:54,880
Master Xuan.

270
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:57,600
Look, even the provincial TV is promoting us now.

271
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:59,000
Our Xuan family's paper

272
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,200
is famous again.

273
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:05,080
Look, Zhang Du even gave a speech onstage.

274
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:08,760
That Zhang Du just loves the spotlight.

275
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:10,360
Well, everyone knows

276
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,600
the ones really running the show behind him

277
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,240
are Old Xuan and Old Man.

278
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:14,080
Exactly.

279
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:15,440
Right, right.

280
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:17,760
If you ask me, these Beijing museum experts

281
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:19,320
don't really know the trade.

282
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:23,000
Zhang Du only studied for a year or so,

283
00:14:23,040 --> 00:14:25,000
thinks he can make Chengxintang paper?

284
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:25,880
Exactly.

285
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:28,840
What kind of talk is that?

286
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:31,600
Zhang Du represents the Xuan family,

287
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,280
not just himself.

288
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:35,400
Yongnian,

289
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:38,320
For something that brings honor to us,

290
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:40,200
you should be the one going.

291
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:41,320
Right, Old Xuan.

292
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:42,360
You should be the one going.

293
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:44,160
Why though?

294
00:14:44,160 --> 00:14:46,080
Chengxintang paper is a technical craft.

295
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:47,240
Why me?

296
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:50,200
Zhang Du is young, let him take it on.

297
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:51,520
What's wrong with that?

298
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:54,280
Chengxintang paper has two major features

299
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:56,760
that the traditional paper we usually make

300
00:14:56,760 --> 00:14:57,720
simply doesn't have.

301
00:14:58,120 --> 00:15:00,760
One is thinness, the other is toughness.

302
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:02,120
The thinness part,

303
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:04,000
with all these experts and professors here,

304
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,160
is actually relatively easier to solve.

305
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:07,320
Hello, Yiran.

306
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:08,280
Sister Xin.

307
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:10,600
Is Xuan Yan doing okay?

308
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:12,680
He's always been easygoing,

309
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:14,160
always laughing and joking,

310
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:15,960
acting like nothing bothers him.

311
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:17,240
Yes.

312
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:19,960
He's set on finding a way forward for Xuan paper.

313
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,280
That's his mission.

314
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:22,280
So,

315
00:15:22,280 --> 00:15:23,720
this time he has to break through

316
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:25,600
his old ideas and experience.

317
00:15:25,680 --> 00:15:26,280
I think

318
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:28,080
this is a rebirth through fire.

319
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:31,000
But I think he's being too impatient right now.

320
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:32,960
I'd like you to go talk some sense into him.

321
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,040
I believe what you say

322
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:35,800
he'll definitely listen to.

323
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:38,360
He might not necessarily listen to me.

324
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:40,600
Alright.

325
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:42,400
I'll find time to pay him a visit.

326
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:45,640
This king of papers, bearing a millennium

327
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:49,600
of heritage, is reborn through the efforts

328
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:51,000
of the Xuan family and Hongxing Factory.

329
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:52,440
Thank you.

330
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:07,320
To bring back Chengxintang paper,

331
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:08,800
which bears a millennium of civilization,

332
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:10,800
to the world once more,

333
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:14,800
is an honor for our group,

334
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:19,200
and even more, it is our weighty

335
00:16:19,680 --> 00:16:22,240
responsibility to inherit and promote

336
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:24,200
China's fine traditional culture.

337
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:25,960
Though the paper is thin,

338
00:16:26,280 --> 00:16:27,160
what it carries

339
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:29,240
is a thousand years of cultural heritage.

340
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:49,480
Are you crazy?

341
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:52,240
Why did you burn it all?

342
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:55,520
I'm asking you a question.

343
00:16:55,520 --> 00:16:56,760
Why did you burn everything?

344
00:16:57,760 --> 00:16:59,880
Out with the old, in with the new.

345
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:05,000
Why didn't you reply to my messages?

346
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,000
Or answer my calls?

347
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:08,000
I was afraid I'd mislead you.

348
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:10,280
Afraid you'd helplessly fall for me,

349
00:17:10,359 --> 00:17:11,359
And wouldn't be able to pull yourself out.

350
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:15,760
You don't have to pretend you don't care.

351
00:17:16,040 --> 00:17:16,960
Everyone has moments when they feel

352
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:18,359
sad and down, you know.

353
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:19,880
So you rushed over today

354
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:21,520
to be my knight in shining armor,

355
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:23,200
planning to rescue me?

356
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:24,880
I'm trying to talk to you seriously.

357
00:17:25,880 --> 00:17:27,119
Help me toss all this in.

358
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:29,880
I know you're hurting inside.

359
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:32,840
You feel that on this path,

360
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,280
no one understands you,

361
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,040
and you're lonely.

362
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:37,000
But if you're willing,

363
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:38,040
you can talk to me.

364
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:40,000
At least I can share some of the burden.

365
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:42,520
At least make you feel that on this path,

366
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:43,840
you're actually not alone.

367
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:45,960
And how do you plan to help me?

368
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:48,040
Me?

369
00:17:48,640 --> 00:17:50,240
I'm Lin Yiran, after all.

370
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:53,360
In all of Taohua Town,

371
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:54,680
I'm the most driven,

372
00:17:55,320 --> 00:17:56,760
most promising young official.

373
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:59,640
I'm out here charging ahead

374
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:00,560
for Taohua Town's Xuan paper industry.

375
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:04,760
Well, that's true.

376
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:12,160
Honestly, I think

377
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:13,640
what you need to do now

378
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:15,440
is to relax,

379
00:18:15,680 --> 00:18:16,520
get out there,

380
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:19,040
and feel what real everyday life is like.

381
00:18:19,560 --> 00:18:22,160
Only then will you know who you're creating for.

382
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:24,720
Broaden your perspective and awareness.

383
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:27,040
This "everyday life" you speak of,

384
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:30,360
why can't I quite grasp what you mean?

385
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:34,240
Just listen to me, that's all.

386
00:18:59,840 --> 00:19:03,000
Honestly, if we're talking credit,

387
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:05,800
I really didn't do all that much.

388
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:07,800
It's our Xuan family ancestors

389
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:09,000
who said it best.

390
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:12,360
Pound jade marrow a thousand times,

391
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:15,240
one Chengxin paper reveals the void.

392
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:16,800
This cup,

393
00:19:17,040 --> 00:19:20,200
I raise to generations of Xuan ancestors.

394
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:22,680
Good, good, good.

395
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:25,120
Zhang Du, eat more food.

396
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:26,280
Drink less.

397
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:27,360
Yes, Shiniang.

398
00:19:27,360 --> 00:19:30,160
This thirty-fifth generation heir,

399
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:32,160
that's over a thousand years.

400
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:35,640
Someone who understands it, values it,

401
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:37,680
and knows how to be grateful,

402
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:40,440
that's all I could ask for.

403
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:43,400
Master, I'll always keep it in my heart.

404
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,800
Though my surname isn't Xuan,

405
00:19:46,440 --> 00:19:47,920
I'm an apprentice of the Xuan family.

406
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:49,120
I am one of the Xuans.

407
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:53,480
Actually, being a Xuan doesn't matter that much.

408
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:54,760
Being an heir...

409
00:19:54,920 --> 00:19:56,600
The new era and the old era

410
00:19:56,760 --> 00:19:58,280
are still different.

411
00:19:58,320 --> 00:20:00,400
You've given your heart to the Xuans,

412
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:01,800
done so much,

413
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:03,720
so you are a Xuan.

414
00:20:05,760 --> 00:20:08,240
Master, I'll always be a Xuan.

415
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:11,000
Good, good.

416
00:20:11,280 --> 00:20:12,320
Sit down.

417
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:15,920
I've had a bit too much to drink.

418
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:18,120
So let me tell everyone,

419
00:20:18,440 --> 00:20:20,720
from this day forward,

420
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:21,920
I can't sit idle.

421
00:20:22,320 --> 00:20:23,640
Because the Xuan family

422
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:26,720
and Songhezhai's two hundred-plus years,

423
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:28,400
we're about to reconnect.

424
00:20:28,680 --> 00:20:32,000
So to preserve the Xuan family's honor,

425
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:33,080
I have to fight for it.

426
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:35,160
So the factory management

427
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:36,480
I'm handing over to Zhang Du.

428
00:20:36,480 --> 00:20:38,680
At this year's ancestral ceremony,

429
00:20:38,680 --> 00:20:40,080
I'll name him as the heir.

430
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:48,520
Did I hear that right?

431
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,280
You heard right,

432
00:20:51,640 --> 00:20:53,320
just not sure if he's drunk.

433
00:20:57,120 --> 00:20:57,920
Old Xuan.

434
00:20:58,760 --> 00:21:00,160
Today,

435
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:03,920
we're mainly celebrating making Chengxintang paper.

436
00:21:04,040 --> 00:21:05,800
Let's not talk about anything else, okay?

437
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:10,200
Old Ye, Zhang Du has done a lot.

438
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,560
He did a good job.

439
00:21:11,720 --> 00:21:13,720
What do you mean, good job?

440
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:15,640
The Chengxintang paper

441
00:21:15,840 --> 00:21:18,360
is your and Master Man's achievement.

442
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:19,680
An apprentice,

443
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:21,560
saying he made Chengxintang paper?

444
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:23,040
If word got out,

445
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:25,680
wouldn't people laugh their heads off? Right?

446
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:28,840
Old Ye, eat something.

447
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:31,600
All right, all right, enough of that.

448
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:33,240
Come on, let's drink.

449
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:37,440
You've all helped me before.

450
00:21:37,760 --> 00:21:38,960
This cup, I raise to all of you.

451
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:42,080
For anything I've done poorly before,

452
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:43,320
or wrong,

453
00:21:43,520 --> 00:21:44,800
please bear with me.

454
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:48,320
I hope from now on we can work together

455
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:50,240
to make the Xuan family better.

456
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:52,400
Come on, let's drink to it.

457
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:55,840
You've all had plenty tonight.

458
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:57,760
That's about enough.

459
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:01,920
Eat, eat.

460
00:22:03,320 --> 00:22:05,480
You've had too much, eat something too.

461
00:22:20,920 --> 00:22:21,720
It's gone viral!

462
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,120
Viral! We're viral!

463
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:24,320
Director! Director!

464
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,280
We're at work. Behave yourself.

465
00:22:26,680 --> 00:22:27,480
Director.

466
00:22:27,560 --> 00:22:30,560
Our video's got over 300,000 views.

467
00:22:30,560 --> 00:22:32,560
The one on Zhang Du making Chengxintang paper.

468
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:35,080
Over 3,000 likes and 3,000 shares.

469
00:22:35,280 --> 00:22:37,720
The account gained over 1,000 followers.

470
00:22:37,960 --> 00:22:39,400
I think it'll keep growing.

471
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,160
Let me take a look.

472
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:41,760
Didn't I see this coming?

473
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:43,920
When I sent you to stake out the Xuan family,

474
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:44,840
you weren't happy about it.

475
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:47,360
No more doubts now, right?

476
00:22:48,120 --> 00:22:49,040
Yes, yes, yes.

477
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:49,840
You're the boss, after all.

478
00:22:49,840 --> 00:22:51,640
A leader is always a leader.

479
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:53,240
Impressive!

480
00:22:53,360 --> 00:22:56,960
You get cocky over the smallest win.

481
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:59,960
If you can't stay level-headed,

482
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:01,760
you'll never achieve anything big.

483
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:04,200
You still expect her to do great things?

484
00:23:04,480 --> 00:23:06,240
She'd rather just be a little internet celebrity.

485
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:07,560
Eat, sleep, sleep, eat.

486
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:09,760
I can hear the jealousy in that.

487
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:11,440
My philosophy in life is,

488
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:13,760
whether it's being an influencer or working,

489
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:15,200
as long as you're happy, that's what matters.

490
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:17,880
Let me tell you a little story.

491
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:18,920
Hold on, Director Liao.

492
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:20,880
I've got a meeting with the Taohua Village director,

493
00:23:20,880 --> 00:23:21,880
and I'm running late.

494
00:23:21,880 --> 00:23:22,640
You two chat.

495
00:23:22,640 --> 00:23:23,760
Drive safe on the way.

496
00:23:23,760 --> 00:23:24,560
You two go on.

497
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:29,320
The Northern Song statesman Fan Zhongyan said,

498
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:32,880
"Not pleased by gain, nor saddened by loss."

499
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:35,600
Back when he was demoted to Dengzhou...

500
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:36,320
Director.

501
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:39,720
I'm not swayed by gains or losses either.

502
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:41,000
Starting today,

503
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:42,760
I'll properly film videos of Taohua Town's

504
00:23:42,760 --> 00:23:44,600
Xuan paper and cultural tourism scenery.

505
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:45,720
I wasn't finished yet.

506
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:46,440
Just hear me out first.

507
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:49,800
If I promote Taohua Town's Xuan paper,

508
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:51,000
wouldn't that be a huge achievement?

509
00:23:51,080 --> 00:23:52,520
And if I make our video account

510
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:54,560
the hottest in the city and county,

511
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:56,080
wouldn't all the credit go to you?

512
00:23:57,080 --> 00:23:58,280
What are you trying to say?

513
00:23:58,440 --> 00:23:59,240
What I'm saying is,

514
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:01,160
I'm off to shoot videos now.

515
00:24:02,680 --> 00:24:04,480
The materials for tomorrow's meeting aren't done yet.

516
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:24,280
I'm not even done eating yet.

517
00:24:25,040 --> 00:24:26,760
By the time you finish nagging and eating,

518
00:24:26,760 --> 00:24:28,280
when am I ever gonna get to sleep?

519
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:30,800
What is it now? What now?

520
00:24:30,840 --> 00:24:32,800
What's got you upset this time?

521
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:39,560
No matter how great other people's kids are,

522
00:24:39,560 --> 00:24:41,320
they belong to other families.

523
00:24:41,760 --> 00:24:43,920
No matter how bad your own kid is,

524
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:45,720
he's still your own flesh and blood.

525
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:48,680
From now on, don't drink so much,

526
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:51,320
running your mouth off without a filter.

527
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:52,480
Can you do that?

528
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:55,880
How is this suddenly my fault again?

529
00:24:56,040 --> 00:24:58,680
It's our own son who refuses to do it.

530
00:24:58,680 --> 00:24:59,960
That's exactly why I said

531
00:25:00,240 --> 00:25:02,240
we should make Zhang Du the successor.

532
00:25:04,600 --> 00:25:05,920
Is it really that our son won't do it?

533
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:08,080
How could he?

534
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:11,000
Have you ever approved of him?

535
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:13,720
From the time he was little,

536
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:15,280
have you ever been satisfied with him?

537
00:25:15,720 --> 00:25:17,440
He's finally taken an interest in something,

538
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:18,840
this Xuan paper cultural product idea,

539
00:25:19,160 --> 00:25:21,520
and you couldn't be more against it,

540
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:23,720
doing everything you can to block him.

541
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:25,720
But have you ever stopped to think,

542
00:25:25,720 --> 00:25:27,520
in your whole life, besides your papermaking,

543
00:25:27,720 --> 00:25:29,280
have you ever cared about anyone?

544
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:31,480
Alright, alright, enough, stop it, okay?

545
00:25:32,320 --> 00:25:35,880
Just let me finish this drink,

546
00:25:35,920 --> 00:25:37,200
have a peaceful meal,

547
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:39,480
and enjoy my drink in peace, okay?

548
00:25:39,920 --> 00:25:40,840
Drink, drink, drink.

549
00:25:42,160 --> 00:25:43,200
I'm done with you.

550
00:25:43,280 --> 00:25:44,480
Drink it or don't, I don't care.

551
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:46,520
You'd better take a good hard look at yourself.

552
00:26:13,440 --> 00:26:14,520
Yongnian.

553
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:16,280
The water pump's acting up again.

554
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:17,680
Still up, I see.

555
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:20,800
This water pump...

556
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:23,600
we've used it for years now.

557
00:26:24,520 --> 00:26:25,320
Yeah.

558
00:26:25,960 --> 00:26:27,520
I was just trying to fix it.

559
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:37,240
Take a look at this.

560
00:26:40,520 --> 00:26:42,440
It's pretty exquisite, isn't it?

561
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:44,160
Xuan Yan made it.

562
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:47,000
Guess how much it sells for.

563
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:48,960
How much?

564
00:26:49,480 --> 00:26:51,000
999 yuan.

565
00:26:51,920 --> 00:26:53,120
Can that actually sell?

566
00:26:53,760 --> 00:26:55,360
You know, this paper...

567
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:58,200
is made from top-grade antique paper.

568
00:26:58,240 --> 00:27:00,360
The price is set a bit too high.

569
00:27:01,240 --> 00:27:03,280
Do you remember, over ten years ago,

570
00:27:04,480 --> 00:27:06,000
we made a few sheets of paper?

571
00:27:06,560 --> 00:27:10,920
That was Qianlong Plum Blossom Jade Paper.

572
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:15,280
What if we used that kind of paper?

573
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:18,760
It'd be great, sure,

574
00:27:19,240 --> 00:27:20,520
but the labor involved...

575
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:21,840
would be enormous.

576
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:23,080
Of course.

577
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:25,600
Otherwise, something this small...

578
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:27,480
how could it sell for 999?

579
00:27:28,160 --> 00:27:30,920
If we used Qianlong Plum Blossom Jade Paper,

580
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:32,080
don't let its size fool you,

581
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:33,960
it'd be worth every penny.

582
00:27:37,320 --> 00:27:39,160
It's a great idea, really.

583
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:42,840
But your son has to give the nod, right?

584
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:26,720
Here, one screen of water.

585
00:28:26,720 --> 00:28:27,720
A bit deeper.

586
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:29,160
Lift.

587
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:30,040
Pour.

588
00:28:32,040 --> 00:28:32,640
Now.

589
00:28:33,320 --> 00:28:33,880
Scoop.

590
00:28:36,040 --> 00:28:36,560
You skinny thing.

591
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:37,480
Look here.

592
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:42,120
Don't keep staring at your own hands.

593
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:43,240
Watch my hands instead.

594
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:44,040
Come on.

595
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:55,440
Follow the height of my hands.

596
00:28:57,200 --> 00:28:57,920
Lift.

597
00:28:58,440 --> 00:28:59,000
Down.

598
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:01,240
When the ancients did things,

599
00:29:01,240 --> 00:29:03,080
they valued a calm, steady mind.

600
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:04,480
No distractions.

601
00:29:05,360 --> 00:29:07,360
Then your movements will have good rhythm.

602
00:29:07,800 --> 00:29:09,480
Not rushed, not chaotic.

603
00:29:17,600 --> 00:29:18,600
Uncle Laokezi.

604
00:29:19,040 --> 00:29:20,760
We've got a little interview here.

605
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:22,240
We'd like to interview you.

606
00:29:22,240 --> 00:29:24,480
Could we shut off the machine first?

607
00:29:25,560 --> 00:29:26,560
Just turn it off.

608
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:31,960
Is that okay?

609
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:33,600
It's a bit too high.

610
00:29:33,600 --> 00:29:34,360
Slightly overexposed.

611
00:29:34,360 --> 00:29:35,520
How about you stand over here?

612
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:38,520
This works, this works.

613
00:29:38,520 --> 00:29:39,520
Got the machine in the shot.

614
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:40,480
Okay.

615
00:29:43,120 --> 00:29:45,480
Uncle, let's turn off the machine first.

616
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:47,760
It's too loud, we can't hear.

617
00:29:49,520 --> 00:29:52,240
Shut it off? Then I'm not working.

618
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:54,160
I'm on the job here.

619
00:29:54,440 --> 00:29:56,000
It's just a quick interview.

620
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:57,880
Won't take long, just turn it off.

621
00:29:57,880 --> 00:29:58,360
Right.

622
00:30:07,720 --> 00:30:09,000
What are you doing?

623
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:10,560
Uncle, take a break first.

624
00:30:11,240 --> 00:30:12,520
We'll be quick.

625
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:14,720
We just want to ask for your advice.

626
00:30:14,840 --> 00:30:15,040
Yeah.

627
00:30:15,040 --> 00:30:15,600
Okay?

628
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:23,680
See, in the old days,

629
00:30:23,840 --> 00:30:27,560
pounding bark, washing stock, making pulp,

630
00:30:27,680 --> 00:30:29,680
it was all done by hand, right?

631
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:31,320
Or with electricity?

632
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:33,720
How far back are you talking?

633
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:35,960
Back when there was no electricity.

634
00:30:36,840 --> 00:30:38,760
You couldn't use it even if you wanted.

635
00:30:38,880 --> 00:30:40,080
That's just how it was.

636
00:30:40,120 --> 00:30:40,920
See, look,

637
00:30:41,240 --> 00:30:43,360
the ancients made such fine paper,

638
00:30:43,360 --> 00:30:44,680
doesn't that just prove

639
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:46,280
handmade is better?

640
00:30:47,040 --> 00:30:48,240
Our ancestors

641
00:30:48,440 --> 00:30:51,080
made paper by hand for thousands of years.

642
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:54,520
Isn't that right, Uncle?

643
00:30:58,080 --> 00:30:59,280
Listen, kid,

644
00:30:59,720 --> 00:31:01,520
they're not even the same ancestors.

645
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:06,360
Want to dig up the past? Go rob a tomb.

646
00:31:08,120 --> 00:31:09,240
This is a paper mill.

647
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:10,520
Little Yu.

648
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:12,240
Master Zhang is kindly teaching you.

649
00:31:12,240 --> 00:31:13,520
Just learn properly.

650
00:31:13,520 --> 00:31:14,280
Exactly.

651
00:31:14,800 --> 00:31:15,520
My master isn't dead yet.

652
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:16,600
Why would I need him to teach me?

653
00:31:16,600 --> 00:31:17,880
Watch what you say.

654
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:19,040
He's the successor now.

655
00:31:19,040 --> 00:31:19,960
The second-in-command.

656
00:31:20,040 --> 00:31:20,840
With Master away,

657
00:31:20,840 --> 00:31:21,800
he calls the shots.

658
00:31:21,800 --> 00:31:22,680
He calls the shots?

659
00:31:23,480 --> 00:31:24,480
I'll eat scallions, I'll eat ginger,

660
00:31:24,480 --> 00:31:25,520
but I draw the line at garlic.

661
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:28,040
Always "ancient methods, ancient methods."

662
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:29,040
How ancients did things...

663
00:31:29,040 --> 00:31:30,000
He saw them?

664
00:31:30,120 --> 00:31:30,800
If he really saw them,

665
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:33,000
tell him to go ask them, then come tell me.

666
00:31:33,440 --> 00:31:35,800
Let us old-timers go find Old Xuan.

667
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:38,240
It can't go on like this.

668
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:40,680
He's got theories on top of theories,

669
00:31:41,040 --> 00:31:43,120
till none of us know how to work anymore.

670
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:47,480
Old friend,

671
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:50,440
Old Xuan still listens to what you say.

672
00:31:50,440 --> 00:31:52,800
You speak up, then we'll all go talk to him.

673
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:54,800
Well, we've got to find him first.

674
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:57,520
He runs off into the mountains every day.

675
00:31:58,320 --> 00:31:59,520
Can't even catch a glimpse of him.

676
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:01,080
Off to the mountains?

677
00:32:01,680 --> 00:32:02,480
What's he doing there?

678
00:32:02,520 --> 00:32:03,320
Right?

679
00:32:04,760 --> 00:32:06,440
Just like that successor of his,

680
00:32:07,080 --> 00:32:08,240
doing "great things," of course.

681
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:11,720
Great things.

682
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:49,680
This water's actually a bit sweet.

683
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:55,480
Talk of Fengyang, sing of Fengyang

684
00:32:55,800 --> 00:32:59,040
Fengyang gave rise to Emperor Zhu

685
00:32:59,440 --> 00:33:03,080
Nine out of ten years bring famine

686
00:33:03,080 --> 00:33:06,440
Rich families sell off their mules

687
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:09,680
Poor families sell their sons

688
00:33:35,600 --> 00:33:36,160
Yongnian.

689
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:38,720
What are you up to?

690
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:40,960
Working out the water diversion.

691
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:44,400
Let me ask you something.

692
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:47,480
If I channel water down from the ravine,

693
00:33:47,480 --> 00:33:50,000
using a fifteen-centimeter pipe,

694
00:33:50,160 --> 00:33:51,040
would that work?

695
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:53,080
I'm no expert on this.

696
00:33:53,360 --> 00:33:54,920
Better ask someone who knows.

697
00:33:55,520 --> 00:33:56,360
Right, right, right.

698
00:33:56,360 --> 00:33:58,480
I really should ask a professional.

699
00:33:59,560 --> 00:34:01,000
Let me pull rank as your elder,

700
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:03,160
and nag you a bit.

701
00:34:03,800 --> 00:34:07,480
You want to resume ties with Songhezhai.

702
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:08,560
That intention,

703
00:34:08,800 --> 00:34:09,679
I understand.

704
00:34:10,480 --> 00:34:14,320
But diverting water, rebuilding pools,

705
00:34:14,320 --> 00:34:16,600
that's a huge investment. Is it worth it?

706
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:21,120
Yongnian.

707
00:34:21,360 --> 00:34:22,560
I'm talking to you.

708
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:24,679
Just a few words,

709
00:34:24,679 --> 00:34:25,480
then I'll be on my way.

710
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:26,239
Hear me out.

711
00:34:26,239 --> 00:34:26,960
I'm listening, listening.

712
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:27,679
My ears are right here.

713
00:34:31,080 --> 00:34:32,600
The folks at our mill

714
00:34:33,120 --> 00:34:34,600
have complaints about Zhang Du.

715
00:34:35,159 --> 00:34:37,320
Young Ye and Master Hu and the others

716
00:34:37,320 --> 00:34:38,679
waited for you after work,

717
00:34:38,679 --> 00:34:39,920
wanting to talk to you.

718
00:34:40,040 --> 00:34:42,239
They waited till dark, but you never came.

719
00:34:45,080 --> 00:34:46,480
What kind of things happened?

720
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:48,040
That Zhang Du kid,

721
00:34:48,239 --> 00:34:50,080
he really sees himself as a master.

722
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:51,480
One minute teaching people this,

723
00:34:51,480 --> 00:34:52,960
next minute teaching them that.

724
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:55,840
And always throwing around "ancient methods,"

725
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:56,960
"the ancestors," this and that.

726
00:34:57,080 --> 00:34:58,880
Our masters have been at it for over ten,

727
00:34:58,880 --> 00:35:00,160
twenty years now.

728
00:35:00,160 --> 00:35:02,520
Now he teaches them the basics like kids.

729
00:35:02,600 --> 00:35:03,720
How's anyone supposed to work like that?

730
00:35:08,320 --> 00:35:10,920
This Zhang Du fellow,

731
00:35:11,520 --> 00:35:12,560
how should I put it?

732
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:13,040
He...

733
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:16,040
He's usually rigid and by-the-book,

734
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:18,840
and a bit of an odd one.

735
00:35:19,280 --> 00:35:21,440
The main thing is his speaking attitude,

736
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:24,840
so conceited, so arrogant,

737
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:26,880
like no one else measures up to him.

738
00:35:27,520 --> 00:35:29,080
It's truly unbearable.

739
00:35:31,680 --> 00:35:34,600
Well, wasn't I the one in charge before?

740
00:35:34,600 --> 00:35:35,680
Everyone was used to that.

741
00:35:35,760 --> 00:35:38,160
Now suddenly a new person's brought in,

742
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:39,840
and folks aren't quite adjusted.

743
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:41,840
Give it some time and it'll be fine.

744
00:35:41,920 --> 00:35:43,520
That's not the main issue.

745
00:35:45,040 --> 00:35:46,560
Naming an heir to the craft,

746
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:50,000
it concerns the roots of our Xuan family,

747
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:51,000
and our honor.

748
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:53,880
You must, must be careful with this.

749
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:56,480
How could I not be careful about this?

750
00:35:56,480 --> 00:35:57,800
The things you say.

751
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:59,680
Fine, fine, you're careful.

752
00:35:59,960 --> 00:36:00,920
But there's one thing

753
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:03,000
I see more clearly than you.

754
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:04,440
This Zhang Du,

755
00:36:04,640 --> 00:36:06,440
he's not on your side.

756
00:36:26,360 --> 00:36:28,200
Our Xuan family and Songhezhai

757
00:36:28,440 --> 00:36:30,480
had centuries of partnership in the past.

758
00:36:30,520 --> 00:36:31,600
Then it was broken off.

759
00:36:32,040 --> 00:36:32,880
I've been thinking,

760
00:36:33,480 --> 00:36:35,800
we should revive it in our hands.

761
00:36:36,200 --> 00:36:37,440
The Chengxintang paper

762
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:38,960
brought honor to the Xuan family.

763
00:36:40,120 --> 00:36:41,000
If

764
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:44,440
we can truly partner with Songhezhai now,

765
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:46,360
our strength will grow.

766
00:36:46,600 --> 00:36:49,680
And I'll be worthy as the 35th-gen heir.

767
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:53,280
The Xuan family's paper

768
00:36:53,280 --> 00:36:55,720
has been renowned through the ages,

769
00:36:55,920 --> 00:36:57,440
praised for generations,

770
00:36:57,600 --> 00:36:58,920
thanks to three treasures.

771
00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:01,280
One is the blue sandalwood bark.

772
00:37:01,520 --> 00:37:02,920
Another is sandy-field rice straw.

773
00:37:03,040 --> 00:37:04,480
And the third is mountain spring water.

774
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:07,840
With all of you here, xuan paper's

775
00:37:08,040 --> 00:37:09,480
craftsmanship won't change.

776
00:37:10,280 --> 00:37:12,760
The sandalwood bark and straw won't change either.

777
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:17,320
The only thing that needs to change is the water.

778
00:37:17,480 --> 00:37:19,240
Scientifically speaking,

779
00:37:19,520 --> 00:37:21,400
the spring water in our Xiaoling Village

780
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:22,520
has balanced pH levels

781
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:24,480
and is rich in minerals.

782
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:27,120
It's essential for making fine paper.

783
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:29,880
So do we move the factory up the mountain

784
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:31,000
to use the spring water?

785
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:31,600
No, no, no.

786
00:37:31,600 --> 00:37:32,680
No need to move the factory.

787
00:37:33,720 --> 00:37:34,520
What we'll do

788
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:37,400
is build a reservoir and pipe the water down.

789
00:37:38,160 --> 00:37:39,240
How about this then, Master?

790
00:37:39,520 --> 00:37:40,360
Building the reservoir,

791
00:37:40,720 --> 00:37:42,040
let's do it ourselves.

792
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:44,480
That'll save Master some labor costs.

793
00:37:44,520 --> 00:37:45,200
What do you all think?

794
00:37:45,200 --> 00:37:46,040
Does that work for everyone?

795
00:37:47,400 --> 00:37:48,960
You, our head steward,

796
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:51,640
what kind of muddled math is this?

797
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:53,840
The Xuan family

798
00:37:54,040 --> 00:37:56,080
pays me, the master paper-dryer,

799
00:37:56,320 --> 00:37:57,200
how much a month?

800
00:37:57,520 --> 00:37:59,520
Just wages alone each month,

801
00:37:59,520 --> 00:38:01,880
plus social security, that's 8,000 yuan.

802
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:03,520
If I go work odd jobs,

803
00:38:03,520 --> 00:38:04,640
doing masonry work,

804
00:38:05,200 --> 00:38:07,240
how much wages can that really save?

805
00:38:08,640 --> 00:38:09,520
What he means is,

806
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:11,480
the wallpaper order is finished,

807
00:38:11,480 --> 00:38:13,120
and you don't have anything else to do.

808
00:38:13,120 --> 00:38:15,080
Wouldn't the wages just be given for nothing?

809
00:38:15,200 --> 00:38:17,040
Having you do some masonry work

810
00:38:17,040 --> 00:38:18,640
saves a bit on hired labor.

811
00:38:18,640 --> 00:38:19,840
Get it or not?

812
00:38:19,840 --> 00:38:21,640
No, Sister Sulan, I really didn't mean that.

813
00:38:21,640 --> 00:38:23,200
Isn't that exactly what you meant?

814
00:38:23,400 --> 00:38:25,440
And I didn't say you were wrong either.

815
00:38:25,440 --> 00:38:27,920
We don't have any urgent orders right now.

816
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:29,880
The paper isn't selling well.

817
00:38:29,960 --> 00:38:32,480
Doing some masonry work is no big deal.

818
00:38:32,480 --> 00:38:34,240
We never said we wouldn't do it.

819
00:38:34,360 --> 00:38:35,280
No, I really didn't mean that.

820
00:38:35,360 --> 00:38:35,920
There's no need to deny it.

821
00:38:35,920 --> 00:38:36,640
All right, all right.

822
00:38:37,360 --> 00:38:39,200
We're all family, no need for pretense.

823
00:38:39,520 --> 00:38:41,920
Those willing will work together on it.

824
00:38:41,960 --> 00:38:44,640
Those not willing go scoop and dry paper.

825
00:38:47,520 --> 00:38:48,440
It's settled then.

826
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:50,520
Old Xuan,

827
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:52,000
it's not that I'm unwilling.

828
00:38:53,160 --> 00:38:53,720
Enough.

829
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:06,240
No wonder in the future,

830
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:09,520
he'll be our Xuan family's heir.

831
00:39:10,280 --> 00:39:11,200
Such leadership!

832
00:39:12,200 --> 00:39:17,360
Master Zhang has both brains and brawn.

833
00:39:19,360 --> 00:39:20,360
Master said,

834
00:39:20,840 --> 00:39:22,120
work it if you want,

835
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:23,320
don't work it if you don't, it's fine.

836
00:39:23,600 --> 00:39:24,920
No need for your snide remarks here.

837
00:39:26,080 --> 00:39:27,960
I want to. Not just want to,

838
00:39:27,960 --> 00:39:29,360
I'm especially eager to do it. I...

839
00:39:31,280 --> 00:39:32,320
What's going on?

840
00:39:32,520 --> 00:39:33,200
Here's the thing.

841
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:35,840
I've already hired a few workers.

842
00:39:35,960 --> 00:39:36,880
I'll have them do it.

843
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:38,520
They'll finish in a day or two.

844
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:39,280
Head home.

845
00:39:39,280 --> 00:39:40,400
Everyone pack up and go.

846
00:39:50,920 --> 00:39:52,520
Haven't you gone to rest yet?

847
00:39:53,680 --> 00:39:55,880
Master, I'm not sleepy yet.

848
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:13,640
Have some peanuts your Shiniang roasted.

849
00:40:14,080 --> 00:40:15,440
They smell great.

850
00:40:16,160 --> 00:40:17,080
Thank you, Master.

851
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:23,880
I see.

852
00:40:24,080 --> 00:40:27,000
You're trying to build that paper-pressing

853
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:29,000
wooden lever press, aren't you?

854
00:40:29,720 --> 00:40:31,880
Master, you know your stuff.

855
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:33,080
One look and you knew.

856
00:40:34,520 --> 00:40:36,440
I saw one when I was very young.

857
00:40:38,880 --> 00:40:40,280
What are you doing this for?

858
00:40:41,600 --> 00:40:42,560
For filming.

859
00:40:43,200 --> 00:40:44,320
Taozi's last two episodes

860
00:40:44,320 --> 00:40:46,120
filmed videos on traditional paper-making.

861
00:40:46,560 --> 00:40:48,160
Each one got tens of thousands of views.

862
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:50,520
And lots of customers are asking

863
00:40:50,720 --> 00:40:51,800
where they can buy it.

864
00:40:52,480 --> 00:40:53,760
This wooden press of yours,

865
00:40:54,200 --> 00:40:56,680
compared to the hydraulic jacks we use now,

866
00:40:57,600 --> 00:40:59,280
what's the difference?

867
00:41:02,680 --> 00:41:05,280
In the old days, we used the wooden press method.

868
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:08,160
Moisture control relied on master's skill.

869
00:41:08,240 --> 00:41:10,760
But now with these hydraulic jacks,

870
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:13,400
pressing is indeed much faster.

871
00:41:13,760 --> 00:41:15,160
And there's a moisture controller,

872
00:41:15,160 --> 00:41:16,800
allowing for precise control.

873
00:41:17,920 --> 00:41:18,440
Here.

874
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:22,720
Come on.

875
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:24,920
But,

876
00:41:25,360 --> 00:41:28,600
I feel it's missing one thing.

877
00:41:29,440 --> 00:41:30,200
That is,

878
00:41:31,760 --> 00:41:33,280
the warmth of paper-making.

879
00:41:35,480 --> 00:41:39,360
So that's why you keep emphasizing traditional paper.

880
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:41,200
Exactly, Master.

881
00:41:41,880 --> 00:41:42,680
I feel that

882
00:41:42,760 --> 00:41:45,440
only handmade ones count as Xuan paper.

883
00:41:45,960 --> 00:41:48,440
Making it requires the right attitude.

884
00:41:48,720 --> 00:41:51,400
You can't mix handmade with mechanical.

885
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:53,880
If one day it's all machine-made,

886
00:41:53,880 --> 00:41:55,400
with no more hand-scooping,

887
00:41:55,560 --> 00:41:58,160
could you still call that Xuan paper?

888
00:41:59,680 --> 00:42:03,120
Well, you do have a point.

889
00:42:05,280 --> 00:42:06,840
But our ancestors,

890
00:42:08,280 --> 00:42:10,160
they weren't set in their ways.

891
00:42:11,120 --> 00:42:12,160
For example,

892
00:42:12,360 --> 00:42:15,000
didn't they invent the water wheel?

893
00:42:15,480 --> 00:42:17,520
That harnesses the power of water

894
00:42:17,960 --> 00:42:19,760
to pound bark and wash pulp.

895
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:22,680
This wooden press of yours,

896
00:42:23,600 --> 00:42:26,680
that came along much later.

897
00:42:27,560 --> 00:42:30,400
What did they use before?

898
00:42:30,640 --> 00:42:35,080
They used huge slabs of bluestone,

899
00:42:35,600 --> 00:42:37,840
so heavy it took five or six men to lift.

900
00:42:37,840 --> 00:42:39,200
And that's where the problem lay.

901
00:42:39,200 --> 00:42:40,560
Because it was too heavy,

902
00:42:40,720 --> 00:42:42,720
there was no way to control

903
00:42:43,320 --> 00:42:44,720
the force applied.

904
00:42:45,880 --> 00:42:46,840
It was uneven,

905
00:42:47,520 --> 00:42:50,080
so what came out of the press

906
00:42:50,080 --> 00:42:51,360
wasn't ideal.

907
00:42:52,400 --> 00:42:53,320
So tell me,

908
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:57,840
are you going to go find slabs that big?
